  "text": "Renal mass reduction. Male Sprague-Dawley rats were anesthetized with a 9:2 mixture of 100 mg/ml ketamine and 10 mg/ml acepromazine (0.1 ml/100 g body wt). As described previously [CITATION_1] , the rats underwent a two-stage procedure in which their total renal mass was reduced by ϳ75%. After recovering from the procedures, all rats with RRM were placed on a high-salt diet (4.0% NaCl; Dyets, Bethlehem, PA) for 3 days to produce RRM-hypertension.",
